I've always loved Sisters' food, so I've been going for years. I would also put others on to experiencing their food as well. Yesterday, we decided to go to Sisters' for Rotis being that we haven't been there since the Pandemic.......we were highly disappointed😑 Four rotis were purchased: shrimp, curry goat, chicken and veggie. Mine was the shrimp.They were tough, ovecooked shrimp; which btw, were burned😟on 1 side of each of the '6' shrimp in the roti. No type of gravey/sauce/moisture. No curry flavor, or any real flavor. It was bland.The roti was crunchy and dry for the most part. There was nothing to this at-ALL. Just disappointment.😒 I was told (and saw for myself) the chicken, as well as the currygoat roti was also dry and lacking flavor. The only reason I gave 2 stars, is because the veggie roti; which also had a side of yams w it, did have a little more flavor to it. Not the usual flavor, but more that the other 3 rotis. Idk about returning after this😏

I told him that I've worked in different restaurant kitchens and am extremely concerned about the health protocols not being followed. A catering disaster!! Sadly this is my 2nd time having a horrible outcome with their catering delivery service. I thought the change in ownership/ management would make the difference but clearly doesn't.  The food was not properly packaged in tightly sealed pans and because heavy items were stacked on top of each other the pans collapsed and all sauce and food spilled out.  The food spill leaked all over the flimsy used box and I wound up cleaning the halls and floors and throwing the food out. I also noticed the food was refrigerator cold - WHO DELIVERS COLD FOOD FOR CATERING (cabbage, yams, rice & peas and codfish) these items should've been hot ready to serve.   The photo shows the mess they delivered to my door and expected me to serve. The cabbage was raw like coleslaw - not cooked or steamed at all and the yams were also undercooked (still hard) and wouldn't have been edible regardless. So much for thanksgiving dinner... They lack professionalism and offer very poor customer service.  I've dined here many times over the years and always regretted giving in to my position to never return. I've tried to forgive their poorly run business over the years: not operating during posted hours; not serving the correct order items; ridiculously small portions; inconsistent and undercooked food,  always cutting corners... I eventually gave up bc it was clear sisters couldn't get it together.  But when both sisters exited the business I thought things would improve - but they are worse now.  To package a catering order the way they did- not taking any effort to properly secure the food was simply incompetent and unacceptable.  They cannot cater point blank bc they dont know what they're doing and don't care to get it right.

I gathered 25-30 of us & met at Sisters' on a Friday afternoon where we had a PHENOMENAL time catching up w/one another, a lot of privacy, superb weather, excellent service & a variety of DIVINE FOOD (my favorite was the curried goat & oxtails)!!! Cozy and quaint neighborhood "spot" with reliably delicious options. Stewed Chicken, Curry Chicken, and Salmon entree are authentic dishes. Mac and Cheese Southern style is a favorite, as well. Don't go when you are in a rush because it takes a few minutes to get your order taken and then 10+ minutes longer to receive your food. There are a few tables to eat-in. Prices are reasonable, but not cheap- the bill can quickly escalate as you add on the sides.
